t.name: description
t.value: Returns any WHO core extensions defined on the given resource with the specified id.

t.name: comment
t.value:
NOTE: Extensions are not the preferred approach, but are used as a way to access
content that is defined by extensions but not yet surfaced in the
CQL model info.

t.name: description
t.value: Returns the single WHO core extension (if present) on the given resource with the specified id.

t.name: comment
t.value:
This function uses singleton from to ensure that a run-time exception is thrown if there
is more than one extension on the given resource with the specified id.
